Reasoning: The paper deals with graph streaming algorithms and their space complexity for finding maximal and maximum independent sets in three different models of graph streams. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves geometric intersection graphs, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The reduction to a multi-party communication problem suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC), and the study of graph problems in streaming models can also be considered under the category of complexity theory (cs.CC).
